Football has its first £1 billion man – but it’s not Beckham, Messi or Ronaldo.

The Mail on Sunday can reveal him to be ‘super-agent’ Jorge Mendes, who has masterminded transfers worth an eye-watering £1,068,370,548 over the course of his career.

Portuguese Mendes, 48, a former nightclub owner who became a football agent 18 years ago, has negotiated £208.5 million worth of signings in the last two months alone.

