Chelsea manager Mourinho says Mendes encourages players to ‘respect their commitments’ to clubs, while former Manchester United boss Sir Alex Ferguson says Mendes is ‘the best agent I dealt with, without a doubt’.

Mendes oversaw two of the summer’s three biggest transfers – of Angel di Maria from Real Madrid to Manchester United, and James Rodriguez from Monaco to Real Madrid.

The son of a gas plant worker, Mendes grew up in Lisbon and had a modest career as a semi-professional footballer before running a nightclub and then becoming an agent.

He now has 58 names on his client list.

 

